<paragraph id="34D9669489DB75629775F3BDBCF2A0E1" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">
<taxonomicName id="FB09EB930293D50B09DBD7A6F8FCBE9D" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis stilbostoma" order="Diaporthales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="stilbostoma">Melanconis stilbostoma</taxonomicName>
(Fr.) Tul. &amp; C. Tul., Select. fung. carpol. (Paris) 2: 115 (1863)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E41889FAE6279121101F189AEC0E9BEF" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" type="notes">
<paragraph id="6942E62E9AED51133083280B958FF8FD" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D517D4D4C37D50F2CAD57BDF8E1D5A76" pageId="10" pageNumber="99">
The type genus 
<taxonomicName id="90940A0E1D4A67B6D8D66710114CD47F" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconis</taxonomicName>
was established by Tulasne and Tulasne (1863) based on 
<taxonomicName id="A2E9C0F749362F966945F4776E1D00A8" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypoxylaceae" genus="Sphaeria" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Sphaeria stilbostoma" order="Xylariales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="stilbostoma">Sphaeria stilbostoma</taxonomicName>
Fr. This genus is characterised by circularly arranged perithecia immersed in well developed to reduced entostromata with a concolourous central column and ostioles erumpent through a light-coloured ectostromatic disc with hyaline, one-septate ascospores; acervuli with light-coloured central column producing brown to olive-brown, fusiform to pyriform alpha conidia and hyaline, cylindrical or allantoid beta conidia (
<bibRefCitation id="1ECEDDF90175A3894EB8C7782B525FB3" author="Barr, ME" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia Memoir" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" pagination="1 - 232" title="The Diaporthales in North America with emphasis on Gnomonia and its segregates." volume="7" year="1978">Barr 1978</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="70A8235760A3EFF09106708A730885A6" author="Castlebury, LA" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" pagination="1017 - 1031" title="A preliminary overview of the Diaporthales based on large subunit nuclear ribosomal DNA sequences." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3761867" volume="94" year="2002">Castlebury et al. 2002</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="90A36FC36E65DFB3B0376BDFB65D6EB0" author="Voglmayr, H" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="22" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 44" title="Multigene phylogeny and taxonomy of the genus Melanconiella (Diaporthales)." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s13225-012-0175-8" volume="57" year="2012">Voglmayr et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="075FA474F8D994D9AD8AB951879CA520" author="Fan, XL" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" url="http://doi.org/10.1007/s11557-016-1163-2" year="2016">Fan et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="0C692939301F6C376CB25121962EDD9C" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconis</taxonomicName>
has approximately 105 species epithets recorded in Index Fungorum (2018), whereas 
<bibRefCitation id="93F9C58997874A21268D46C3CB6F718B" author="Rossman, AY" journalOrPublisher="Mycoscience" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" pagination="135 - 144" title="A review of the phylogeny and biology of the Diaporthales." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10267-007-0347-7" volume="48" year="2007">Rossman et al. (2007)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that many of the species previously residing in 
<taxonomicName id="7DB2A97685062ED142FE6E09E5E1743A" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Melanconis</taxonomicName>
may belong somewhere else. 
<bibRefCitation id="6B7571B597CCAB0F76F4801AE98DC87D" author="Fan, XL" journalOrPublisher="Persoonia" pageId="21" pageNumber="110" url="http://doi.org/10.1007/s11557-016-1163-2" year="2016">Fan et al. (2016)</bibRefCitation>
provided an account on this genus including five species (
<taxonomicName id="E19224B07C72DE0FB595DA713771E6AD" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Melanconidaceae" genus="Melanconis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Melanconis alni" order="Diaporthales" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="alni">Melanconis alni</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="DBF4E9716BB7DFBAEE8FD489E7B742DD" genus="Ms." lsidName="Ms. betulae" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="betulae">Ms. betulae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CAF7A23AB9E19326FB8A0C84DA36DB45" genus="Ms." lsidName="Ms. marginalis" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="marginalis">Ms. marginalis</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="EAF7A567812A1650FBF293E7CAA87467" genus="Ms." lsidName="Ms. itoana" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="itoana">Ms. itoana</taxonomicName>
and the type species 
<taxonomicName id="EA581DE167631D1481836C2F400B32CF" genus="Ms." lsidName="Ms. stilbostoma" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" rank="species" species="stilbostoma">Ms. stilbostoma</taxonomicName>
), which were restricted to hosts in 
<taxonomicName id="ABF363AF5C4DA17AC1F9EBC7B018F0A8" family="Betulaceae" genus="Melanoconiellaceae" lsidName="Melanoconiellaceae" pageId="10" pageNumber="99" rank="family">Betulaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
